        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Israeli strikes on Lebanon: Tel Aviv seeks to 'eliminate Hezbollah' Middle East Issued on: 06/03/2026 - 10:59 The Israeli military said on Friday it had begun fresh strikes against Iran‑backed Hezbollah in the southern suburbs of Beirut, a Hezbollah stronghold targeted after a mass evacuation order for local residents. “One of Israel’s goals is to allow residents of northern Israel along the Lebanese border to live in peace,” FRANCE 24’s Noga Tarnopolsky said, adding that Israel is also seeking to “eliminate Hezbollah” amid the militant group’s deep unpopularity among many Lebanese as the conflict escalates. Nadim Houry: Middle East being overrun by 'madmen' showing total disregard for international law 06/03/2026 Middle East Trump urges Iranian diplomats around the world to request asylum 05/03/2026 Middle East Israel strikes Beirut’s southern suburbs after issuing a blanket evacuation order 05/03/2026 Middle East Seafarers can refuse to sail through Mideast Gulf region, main union says 05/03/2026 Middle East Israeli army announces start of airstrikes on southern Beirut suburb 05/03/2026 Middle East Trump unlikely to ever commit ground US forces to Iran, expert says 05/03/2026 Middle East US claims Iran's missile capabilities 'severely degraded' 05/03/2026 Middle East Qatar says 14 ballistic missiles and 4 drones intercepted 05/03/2026 Middle East US war on Iran has no Plan B, warns Scott Lucas: 'Trump just wants to kill people and blow stuff up' 05/03/2026 Middle East"
